This is INSIDE-OUT, a CS thesis project at University of San Carlos (DCISM).
Binary emotion classification (HAPPY vs SAD) from offline scanned handwriting
and drawing samples using a CNN-HMM hybrid architecture.

Researcher: Cyrel Jane A. Edaño
Adviser: Christian V. Maderazo, M.Eng.
GitHub: https://github.com/Yeeejj/EMHA

RAW DATASET STRUCTURE:
- respondent_001/ through respondent_NNN/ on local desktop
- Each has PNG/ (4 files) and PDF/ (4 files)
- Files named EMHA{YYYYMMDD}_{HHMMSSff}.ext
- Alphabetical sort = page order: index 0=cover, 1=selfreport, 2=drawing, 3=writing
- Barcode rule: respondent_001 → P001 (strip prefix, zero-pad, prepend P)

ASSESSMENT STRUCTURE (FINALE):
- Page 2: 24-item Likert self-report (1-5), ground truth label source
- Page 3: 2x2 drawing grid (circles, dots, person, house)
- Page 4: 5x3 word table (Content/Melancholic/Optimistic/Disconnected/Vibrant
  × Left/Right/Uppercase) + 5 cursive sentence rows

CODING CONVENTIONS:
- PyTorch only, no TensorFlow
- All hyperparameters in config.py via dataclasses
- Run modules from project root: python -m src.*
- black + flake8 for formatting
- Do NOT modify DATA/SPLITS/test/ until final evaluation
- Fix known bug in hybrid.py before any training: HMMClassifier
  called with unsupported n_features argument

KEY FILES:
- CLAUDE.md: project conventions
- SYSTEMS_GUIDE.md: full architecture documentation
- config.py: all hyperparameters and paths
- DATA/METADATA/: all CSV manifests